*** EFS -- Elastic File Syatem ***

-- Amazon Elastic File System (Amazon EFS) provides serverless, fully elastic file storage 
so that we can share file data without provisioning or managing storage capacity and performance.
--  It is designed to be highly available, durable, and scalable, making it ideal for a wide range of applications
-- Amazon EFS has a simple web services interface, we can create and configure file systems quickly and easily
-- Amazon EFS is accessible across most types of Amazon Web Services compute instances, 
including Amazon EC2, Amazon ECS, Amazon EKS, AWS Lambda, and AWS Fargate.


*** How to create EFS :
-- click on create file system --- name --- select VPC 

*** How to create Access Point 
-- add File system ID -- User ID & Group ID -- owner User ID & Owner Group ID  all set like same === 1001
-- add permission 0777

